<MudContainer>

   
    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <div class="faq-section">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Align="Align.Center" GutterBottom="true">
            Frequently Asked Questions
        </MudText>

        <MudText Class="faq-question">1. What are the benefits of using Clarity Crate over ChatGPT?</MudText>
        <MudText Class="faq-answer">
            Clarity Crate is designed for efficient text summarization, focusing on key points and concise formatting. Unlike ChatGPT, which generates text based on free-form prompts, Clarity Crate is specialized for summarizing business reports, academic articles, and content like podcasts or meetings. Plus, we support OCR for scanned PDFs!
        </MudText>

        <MudText Class="faq-question">2. How long does it take to summarize text?</MudText>
        <MudText Class="faq-answer">
            The first time you summarize, it may take 25-30 seconds due to server initialization. Apologies for the wait—this is because we use a free server for the model. After the initial run, summaries will take just 5-10 seconds!
        </MudText>

        <MudText Class="faq-question">3. Can I summarize multiple documents at once?</MudText>
        <MudText Class="faq-answer">
            At the moment, Clarity Crate processes one document at a time. However, we’re working on expanding this functionality, so multi-document summarization is coming soon!
        </MudText>

        <MudText Class="faq-question">4. What types of documents can be summarized?</MudText>
        <MudText Class="faq-answer">
            Clarity Crate can summarize virtually any text-based document, including PDFs, Word documents, meeting notes, academic papers, and more. We even support scanned PDFs thanks to OCR technology.
        </MudText>
    </div>
</MudContainer>











